  • Constructor Details

    • Appointment

      public Appointment​(int appointmentId, java.lang.String title, java.lang.String description, java.lang.String location, java.lang.String type, java.lang.String start, java.lang.String end, java.lang.String createDate, java.lang.String createdBy, java.lang.String lastUpdate, java.lang.String lastUpdatedBy, int customerId, int userId, java.lang.String contactName)
      This is the constructor for the Appointment objects.
      Parameters:
      appointmentId - A unique Identifier integer.
      contactName - Holds the name of the contact who is responsible for this appointment.
      createDate - The exact time the appointment was first created.
      createdBy - Which user created this appointment.
      customerId - A unique Identifier for which customer is assigned to this appointment.
      description - A short collection of text to describe the appointment.
      lastUpdate - A date when this appointment was last updated.
      end - When this appointment will end.
      start - When this appointment will begin.
      location - The address where this appointment will take place.
      title - The title of this appointment.
      type - What category of appointment this falls into.
      lastUpdatedBy - The last user to update this appointment, not the user who created it.
      userId - The user associated with the appointment.

    • populateList

      public static void populateList()
      Uses a LAMBDA expression to refresh the database appointments with the UI Observable List. Calling this will keep the List up to date. This is used for keeping table views up to date and accurate. If this is not called, the UI and database will not have matching data.

    • populateListFromModify
